<br>
So saying its a good thing to make primal rare now is worthles in my opinion, ST has been for too long easy to get primal from, so everyone with primal can go 'sure make it harder, this is too good for how easy it is' but the poeple that dont have it yet are going 'hey wtf, he got it easy cause he was faster to it and now we get it hard'.<br>
<br>
And as for faction, I bet the guy that posted above reflecting NToV to ST has NToV loot, and prolly a primal. Look at it this way, youre a guild that can do vindi/lendi type mobs, but cant do most very often because other guilds constantly monopolize the camps, so giving that situation your guild decides to go off of dragon faction and onto giant faction because of ST mobs, verant goes 'oh yeah, now you get +cov from going there, *thumbs up*' and totally screws the entire guild from what they had planned around this zone.<br>
and as for 20 keys for named in st now, thats crap too, I do like the idea of them dropping more than one primal at a time, but with as many guilds as we have on zebuxoruk trying to get into ST as fast as they can, and the occasinal big guild smashing dragons just because theyre up, makes it very hard to get in there if youre not a ruthless guild that doesnt care about stomping over another guild to Zlandicar, and manaburners are the added twist, we got &quot;team manaburn&quot; on our server composed of 20+ wizards that kill anything from gore in dreadlands, to sont guarding tov, so with all that compitition, its going to be even harder to get in.<br>
<br>
